{"title_page": "Jim Freund", "text_new": "{{third-party|date=May 2017}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2014}}\n[[File:Jim Freund.jpg|thumb|'''Jim Freund''']]\n\n'''Jim Freund''' is a radio personality and a prominent figure in the [[speculative fiction]] community as host of the Pacifica Radio show [https://www.wbai.org/program.php?program=70 Hour of the Wolf] and as  [[curator]] of the [[New York Review of Science Fiction|New York Review of Science Fiction Reading Series]].<ref name=\"WBAI Official Site\">[http://wbai.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=380&Itemid=135 WBAI Official Site]</ref><ref name=\"hourwolf.com\">[http://www.hourwolf.com/nyrsf/index.htm New York Review of Science Fiction Reading Series]</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nFreund lives in [[Brooklyn]], New York with his partner, tech editor and author [[Barbara Krasnoff]] and \"lots of toy penguins.\"<ref name=\"Freund\">[http://readercon.org/bios/freund.htm Readercon biography of Jim Freund].</ref><ref name=\"ClockworkPhoenix4\">\"The Authors: Barbara Krasnoff\" in ''Clockwork Phoenix 4'', Mythic Delirium Books, Roanoke VA, 2013, p. 268.</ref><ref name=\"ClockworkPhoenix5\">\"The Authors: Barbara Krasnoff\" in ''Clockwork Phoenix 5'', Mythic Delirium Books, Roanoke VA, 2016, p. 259.</ref>\n\n==Career==\nAs host and producer of [[Hour of the Wolf (radio show)|Hour of the Wolf]] (created by [[Margot Adler]]), which has aired on [[WBAI]] in New York City since 1974, Freund has presented the work of and interviewed many major figures in [[speculative fiction]]. As [[curator]] of the [[New York Review of Science Fiction|New York Review of Science Fiction Reading Series]] he has been responsible for the presentation of a long-running series of live readings by major figures of [[speculative fiction]].<ref name=\"WBAI Official Site\"/><ref name=\"hourwolf.com\"/><ref>[http://www.hourwolf.com/hotw/ Hour of the Wolf: Upcoming Programs/Past Guests]</ref>\n\nHe also has a deep interest in the stage and has produced three plays off-off-Broadway.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.hourwolf.com Hour of the Wolf, Official Site]\n* [http://www.nyrsf.com New York Review of Science Fiction, Official Site]\n*https://brooklyneagle.com/articles/2019/06/10/hour-of-the-wolf-sci-fi-radio/\n*https://www.blackgate.com/2019/05/29/power-couples-in-the-world-of-speculative-fiction-jim-freund-and-barbara-krasnoff/\n\n{{PacificaRadio}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Freund, Jim}}\n[[Category:Radio personalities from New York City]]\n[[Category:American radio producers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Pacifica Foundation people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{third-party|date=May 2017}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2014}}\n[[File:Jim Freund.jpg|thumb|'''Jim Freund''']]\n\n'''Jim Freund''' is a radio personality and a prominent figure in the [[speculative fiction]] community as host of the Pacifica Radio show [https://www.wbai.org/program.php?program=70 Hour of the Wolf] and as  [[curator]] of the [[New York Review of Science Fiction|New York Review of Science Fiction Reading Series]].<ref name=\"WBAI Official Site\">[http://wbai.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=380&Itemid=135 WBAI Official Site]</ref><ref name=\"hourwolf.com\">[http://www.hourwolf.com/nyrsf/index.htm New York Review of Science Fiction Reading Series]</ref>\n\nAs host and producer of [[Hour of the Wolf (radio show)|Hour of the Wolf]] (created by [[Margot Adler]]), which has aired on [[WBAI]] in New York City since 1974, Freund has presented the work of and interviewed many major figures in [[speculative fiction]]. As [[curator]] of the [[New York Review of Science Fiction|New York Review of Science Fiction Reading Series]] he has been responsible for the presentation of a long-running series of live readings by major figures of [[speculative fiction]].<ref name=\"WBAI Official Site\"/><ref name=\"hourwolf.com\"/><ref>[http://www.hourwolf.com/